            { id:"i-ow-4", title:"Cardinality — how many values a property can have",
              detail:"owl:exactCardinality 1 means exactly one value. owl:minCardinality 1 means at least one. owl:maxCardinality 3 means no more than three. A Patient must have exactly one blood type: :Patient owl:onProperty :bloodType ; owl:exactCardinality 1 . The reasoner enforces this on every patient instance." },
            { id:"i-ow-5", title:"SWRL rules — writing IF/THEN in OWL",
              detail:"SWRL (Semantic Web Rule Language) is the standard for IF/THEN rules in OWL. Syntax: Patient(?p) ^ takesMedication(?p, ?d1) ^ interactsWith(?d1, ?d2) ^ prescribes(?doc, ?d2) → Alert(?a) ^ involves(?a, ?p). Read it left to right: if all conditions hold, then the conclusions are inferred. Protégé has a SWRL editor built in." },
