              detail:"SELECT ?patient ?drug WHERE { ?patient a :Patient . ?patient :takesMedication ?drug . ?drug :interactsWith ?other . } Variables start with ?. The WHERE block describes the pattern to find. The query returns every patient-drug pair where the drug interacts with something. No JOINs — just pattern matching." },
            { id:"i-sp-2", title:"FILTER — narrowing results with conditions",
              detail:"FILTER(?age > 65) keeps only elderly patients. FILTER(STR(?name) = 'John') matches by name. FILTER NOT EXISTS { ?p :hasConsent true } finds patients without consent records. FILTER goes inside the WHERE block. You can combine multiple FILTERs. Use LANG(?label) = 'en' to filter by language tag." },
